==Finnish==
{{Finnish index|p|i}}

===Etymology===
From {{inh|fi|fiu-fin-pro|*pitädäk}}, from {{inh|fi|fiu-pro|*pitä-}}. Cognate with {{cog|et|pidama}}, {{cog|myv|педямс|sc=Cyrl}}, {{cog|hu|fűz||to tie}}.

===Pronunciation===
{{fi-pronunciation|*}}

===Verb===
{{fi-verb}}

# {{lb|fi|transitive|_|+ partitive}} to [[hold]], [[grasp]], [[grip]]
#: {{uxi|fi|Minä voin '''pitää''' laukkuasi.|I can '''hold''' your bag.}}
# {{lb|fi|transitive|_|+ accusative}} to [[keep]], [[take]]
#: {{uxi|fi|'''Pidän''' tämän sisiliskon.|I '''will keep''' this lizard.}}
# {{lb|fi|transitive|_|+ elative}} to [[like]], [[be]] [[fond]] of
#: {{uxi|fi|Minä '''pidän''' appelsiineista.|I '''like''' oranges.}}
#: {{uxi|fi|'''Pidän''' omenoista enemmän kuin appelsiineista.|I '''prefer''' apples to oranges.|lit=I '''like''' apples more than oranges.}}
#: {{syn|fi|tykätä}}
#: {{ant|fi|inhota|vihata}}
# {{lb|fi|transitive|impersonal|genitive + 3rd-pers. singular + 1st infinitive}} to [[have]] (to do); (''in conditional mood'') [[should]] (do), [[ought]] (to do), [[be]] [[suppose]]d (to do), [[would]] [[have]] (to do)
#: {{uxi|fi|Sinun '''pitää''' mennä töihin.|You '''have''' to go to work.}}
#: {{uxi|fi|Meidän '''pitäisi''' mennä töihin.|We '''should''' go to work.}}
# {{lb|fi|transitive|_|+ partitive + essive}} to [[consider]] (to be), to [[assess]], to [[see]] as
#: {{uxi|fi|Minä '''pidän''' ihmis'''iä''' vihamielisi'''nä'''.|I '''consider''' people to be hostile.}}
# {{lb|fi|transitive|_|+ elative + [[kiinni]]}} to [[hold]] [[onto]]
#: {{uxi|fi|Minä voin '''pitää''' laukustasi '''kiinni'''.|I can '''hold onto''' your bag.}}
# {{lb|fi|transitive|_|+ partitive}} to [[keep]] {{gloss|an animal}}
#: {{uxi|fi|Korkeasaaressa '''pidetään''' monenlaisia eläimiä.|Many types of animals '''are kept''' in Korkeasaari Zoo.}}
# {{lb|fi|transitive}} to [[hold]], to [[organize]] {{gloss|such as an event}}
# {{lb|fi|transitive}} {{n-g|Used in very many collocations with nouns, translated often as "[[engage]] in", "[[have]]", "[[do]]", "[[transact]]", "[[pursue]]", "[[conduct]]", "[[carry out]]" "[[keep up]]", "[[maintain]]", "[[lead]]/[[teach]]" etc.}}
#: {{uxi|fi|Hän '''piti''' kuulustelua syytetylle.|S/he '''was conducting''' an interrogation of the accused.}}
#: {{uxi|fi|'''Pidän''' SAP-kurssia.|I '''teach''' a SAP course.}}

====Usage notes====
* {{sense|to have to}} {{m|fi|täytyä|Täytyä}} expresses '''''absolute''''' necessity to do something, whereas ''pitää'' does not have such an unconditional sense as {{m|fi||täytyä}}.
* {{sense|to like, be fond of}} With verbs, a derived noun (such as with {{m|fi|-minen}}, valid for all verbs) in elative case must be used.

